      "content": "i get that, but just being real, i've heard that in those bigger, more diverse cities the schools can sometimes be a bit all over the place or less controlled. like, is there a general trend where the more diverse or urban districts tend to have more issues with safety or lower academic standards compared to the more homogeneous ones? i just want to be prepared for what we might actually be walking into.",
